I'm a linux and software junkie. So I'm constantly installing, uninstalling and tweaking software. I don't recommend constantly repairing a system...but this BEAST for what it is and the price tag...seems to be able to more than take it. I'm more than happy with this purchase. I don't usually leave reviews...so...would I recommend this Laptop? Yes. Will it run a few programs simultaneously? Yes. Will it run Minecraft? Yes. Will it run Battlefield? Real Buggy...Yes. Will it run VR? No. Can you run Debian and Windows side-by-side? YES. Can you run Video or Music editing software? Yes. Can you stream on YouTube? Yes. Can you rock out that mid-term essay you left for last minute, while hopped up on Spicy Ramen and Red bulls at 3 a.m.? You Betcha'. All in all if you're looking for a cheap priced laptop to do some work, that doesn't involve competitive gaming, or Launch codes programming, give this one a try. Besides...that 30 day Walmart return policy doesn't sit too bad either...üòÅ

reviews.title: No Regrets!
reviews.review_text: To say I was hesitant on this purchase would be an understatement. When I saw the price I truly believed there was a mistake. I had just started college again and knew that I needed a Windows Accessible laptop to complete my assignments throughout the semester. I read all the reviews and made the executive decision to try knowing that any of the negative references could be true! To my luck everything about this purchase was easy! The shipping was fast, I got the laptop delivered to me in 2 days respectfully placed on my porch. When opening the box, the first thing I noticed was the charger and the laptop in very nice condition and protected. I took both items out and opened the laptop immediately to go through and setup login information. The battery was 3/4 of the way charged and what would be considered the mouse, worked and continues to work perfectly! There's a camera cover as well that slides when you need to access the camera. I have owned this laptop now for three weeks and so far have no regrets. I am able to get all of my schoolwork done and sent to my professors stress free! I highly recommend this product and I hope you get the same great service I did!

reviews.title: Avoid
reviews.review_text: Review: I regret buying this Intel Celeron laptop. From the moment I turned it on, it felt painfully slow. Basic tasks like opening a browser, checking email, or switching between tabs take forever. It lags constantly, freezes at random, and even struggles to stream videos smoothly. The Celeron processor is just too underpowered for modern use. Even with light workloads, it crawls. If you're hoping to use this for anything beyond typing a Word doc, you'll be disappointed. Multi-tasking? Forget about it. Loading updates? Go make a sandwich while it thinks about it. To make matters worse, the return process has been an absolute nightmare. Endless hoops, poor communication, and delays at every step. It's like they know the product is bad and want to make sure you give up before actually sending it back. The build might look okay on the outside, but performance-wise this laptop feels outdated right out of the box. Honestly, your phone will run faster. Spend a little more for at least an Intel i3 or AMD Ryzen ‚Äì you'll thank yourself later. Bottom line: This thing is cheap for a reason. It's basically a frustration machine, and even trying to return it is its own headache
